Well, let me see if Xile is at home.

258
00:18:44,120 --> 00:18:47,999
I'll ask her get it. She can also help me try it on.

259
00:18:51,320 --> 00:18:54,140
Why isn't anyone answering the phone?

260
00:18:54,140 --> 00:18:56,310
Well, I'll go back and take a look.

261
00:18:58,476 --> 00:19:00,980
- Go back first.
- Okay.

262
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:40,939
Good morning.

263
00:19:40,939 --> 00:19:42,439
Morning.

264
00:19:43,179 --> 00:19:45,680
When are you going to work today?

265
00:19:45,680 --> 00:19:47,959
I'm not working today.

266
00:20:18,560 --> 00:20:21,140
Whose pillow is this?

267
00:20:25,660 --> 00:20:29,080
So forgetful. No wonder no one answered the call.

268
00:20:29,080 --> 00:20:31,019
Baby.

269
00:20:31,019 --> 00:20:33,520
- Baby. Baby, are you home?
- My Mom.

270
00:20:33,520 --> 00:20:37,639
Oh no! Didn't you say they would be back after a long while? Why did they suddenly come back?

271
00:20:37,639 --> 00:20:39,620
How should I know?

272
00:20:40,760 --> 00:20:43,360
- Hurry, hurry.
- Baby.

273
00:20:46,079 --> 00:20:50,200
- No, no. Ding Ran, you find a place to hide first.
- I...

274
00:20:50,980 --> 00:20:54,400
- Baby.
- Hurry, get off, get off.

275
00:20:57,879 --> 00:20:59,960
- Baby.
- Mom.

276
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:02,120
You haven't gotten up yet?

277
00:21:02,680 --> 00:21:05,679
I worked too late yesterday. I was in a deep sleep.

278
00:21:05,679 --> 00:21:08,740
Did you work all night again?

279
00:21:08,740 --> 00:21:11,019
I miss you so much.

280
00:21:12,520 --> 00:21:15,999
- I miss you too.
- I miss you so much.

281
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:20,340
The sun is shining so brightly. You didn't even close the curtains.

282
00:21:20,340 --> 00:21:21,899
Mom!

283
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:26,680
- My stomach hurts a bit all of a sudden.
- Are you okay?

284
00:21:26,680 --> 00:21:28,900
Can you help me get some medicine from next door?

285
00:21:28,900 --> 00:21:32,280
- Okay, okay, just wait for me to fetch it.
- Okay.

286
00:21:35,919 --> 00:21:39,659
Ding Ran, Ding Ran.

287
00:21:40,700 --> 00:21:42,320
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

288
00:21:42,320 --> 00:21:44,279
Our love is normal.

289
00:21:44,279 --> 00:21:46,680
- Why is it like—
- Baby. -
- Mom.

290
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:48,659
What's wrong again?

291
00:21:48,659 --> 00:21:53,260
Well, do you have time to help me get a ring?

292
00:21:53,260 --> 00:21:57,160
- I'm free, I'm free.
- Never mind, you have a stomachache.

293
00:21:57,160 --> 00:22:00,899
Mom, actually, my stomachache is from hunger.

294
00:22:00,899 --> 00:22:03,299
- Can you find something for me to eat?
- Okay.

295
00:22:03,299 --> 00:22:06,200
- I'll go find something to eat for you.
- Okay.

296
00:22:12,839 --> 00:22:16,300
- Find something I like to eat.
- Okay.

297
00:22:27,139 --> 00:22:28,868
Ding Ran.

298
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:33,040
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

299
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:37,360
Hug, hug.

300
00:22:40,220 --> 00:22:42,240
I'm sorry.

301
00:22:43,239 --> 00:22:44,880
Don't go back for now.

302
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:48,539
Why? Can't bear to part with me?

303
00:22:48,539 --> 00:22:52,100
If we appear at the same time, it would seem suspicious.

304
00:22:52,100 --> 00:22:56,440
So, you should go hang out with Qi Fei for a few hours and then go back.

305
00:22:56,440 --> 00:23:00,120
Jiang Xile, don't go too far.

306
00:23:04,039 --> 00:23:09,320
I have to go to the store to get a ring for my Mom this afternoon. So, let's meet outside. Okay?

307
00:23:09,320 --> 00:23:11,139
Okay.

308
00:23:11,139 --> 00:23:13,640
I'll listen to you.

309
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:15,219
- I'm leaving.
- Okay.

310
00:23:15,219 --> 00:23:17,520
Don't let my Mom see you.

311
00:23:19,919 --> 00:23:22,099
- Bye, I'm off.
- Bye.

312
00:23:32,020 --> 00:23:34,719
Lu Liuliu.

313
00:23:36,480 --> 00:23:39,520
What! You're pregnant?

314
00:23:43,039 --> 00:23:45,240
- We are leaving.
- Bye-bye.

315
00:23:45,240 --> 00:23:47,620
- Bye.
- Bye.

316
00:23:54,119 --> 00:23:59,919
Jiang Xile, how can someone as irresponsible as me become a mother?

317
00:23:59,919 --> 00:24:02,639
You're actually quite responsible.

318
00:24:04,520 --> 00:24:08,739
Can you imagine someone like me becoming a mother?

319
00:24:08,739 --> 00:24:11,559
It's indeed a bit hard to imagine.

320
00:24:11,559 --> 00:24:14,039
Have you told Qi Fei?

321
00:24:15,560 --> 00:24:20,960
I'm afraid once I tell him, he will definitely try to marry me.

322
00:24:20,960 --> 00:24:22,239
What should I do?

323
00:24:22,239 --> 00:24:26,840
If you marry Qi Fei, you should be very happy.

324
00:24:27,879 --> 00:24:30,480
What if we divorce?

325
00:24:31,680 --> 00:24:34,539
What about my child after the divorce?

326
00:24:34,539 --> 00:24:39,399
Won't I become an irresponsible parent like my parents?

327
00:24:39,399 --> 00:24:42,179
What should I do?

328
00:24:45,899 --> 00:24:47,692
Liuliu.

329
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:54,600
When Ding Ran's father on his way home from grocery shopping every weekend, he always buys a bouquet of flowers for my mom.

330
00:24:54,600 --> 00:24:58,740
My mom would be very happy to put it in the vase.

331
00:24:58,740 --> 00:25:05,640
They made me feel that what children need most was not a tied-up family, but loving parents.

332
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:08,920
You and Qi Fei will definitely be loving parents.

333
00:25:08,920 --> 00:25:11,019
Why don't you give it a try?

334
00:25:13,780 --> 00:25:15,699
Really?

335
00:25:15,699 --> 00:25:17,719
Definitely.

336
00:25:19,720 --> 00:25:23,539
Well, I'll try telling him.

337
00:25:23,539 --> 00:25:25,560
Tell him.

338
00:25:50,959 --> 00:25:52,979
So comfortable.

339
00:25:54,919 --> 00:25:58,280
What's up? Why did you suddenly want to ride my motorcycle with me today?

340
00:25:58,280 --> 00:25:59,460
Nothing much.

341
00:25:59,460 --> 00:26:04,419
I just want to ask, at what age is it best for a child to learn to ride a motorcycle?

342
00:26:05,320 --> 00:26:07,600
This depends on individual abilities and interests.

343
00:26:07,600 --> 00:26:10,520
Why, do you have a friend's child who wants to learn?

344
00:26:10,520 --> 00:26:15,800
No. I was just thinking if I had a child in the future

345
00:26:15,800 --> 00:26:20,779
and if he wanted to learn to ride a motorcycle, should I support or oppose it?

346
00:26:21,800 --> 00:26:23,959
Why are you laughing?

347
00:26:23,959 --> 00:26:27,460
Your child probably will be like you, not even able to ride a bicycle.

348
00:26:27,460 --> 00:26:30,739
Qi Fei, let's not see each other for three days.

349
00:26:30,739 --> 00:26:35,080
Liuliu, not being able to ride a bike is not a big deal.

350
00:26:35,080 --> 00:26:38,840
Do you want to learn? I can teach you, Liuliu.

351
00:26:40,179 --> 00:26:41,759
Liuliu.

352
00:26:41,759 --> 00:26:46,419
Liuliu, I won't say you can't ride a bike anymore.

353
00:26:47,440 --> 00:26:49,920
It's just fixing this.

354
00:26:50,530 --> 00:26:52,810
Your Highness.

355
00:26:54,299 --> 00:26:58,280
Xile, it's so late, but your Mom still hasn't come over for dinner.

356
00:26:58,280 --> 00:27:02,059
She's still staring at her ring. She'll be here soon.

357
00:27:02,059 --> 00:27:04,920
Okay, let her stare at it a bit longer. We'll wait for her.

358
00:27:04,920 --> 00:27:08,020
Baby, are you pregnant?

359
00:27:09,839 --> 00:27:11,680
What are you talking about, Mom?

360
00:27:11,680 --> 00:27:14,779
I found these books in your room.

361
00:27:15,680 --> 00:27:18,219
Newborn Care Guide.

362
00:27:18,219 --> 00:27:21,959
Baby, it's okay. I can accept it.

363
00:27:21,959 --> 00:27:25,440
Who is it? Do I know him?

364
00:27:26,580 --> 00:27:29,080
- So quick to get pregnant?
- What are you stirring up?

365
00:27:29,080 --> 00:27:31,640
Stay away.

366
00:27:31,640 --> 00:27:35,000
Xile, when did you start dating?

367
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:38,559
Yeah. When will you bring him home to meet us?

368
00:27:38,559 --> 00:27:43,320
No need to bring him. I'm right in front of you.

369
00:27:44,139 --> 00:27:46,619
It's still Xiao Zhang, right?

370
00:27:47,800 --> 00:27:49,979
None of his business.

371
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:53,440
Xile, I can take care of a baby.

372
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:56,580
Dad, you're thinking too far ahead.

373
00:27:56,580 --> 00:28:00,259
It's not me, it's not me. Calm down, everyone.

374
00:28:00,259 --> 00:28:02,800
Really? Then who is it?

375
00:28:02,800 --> 00:28:05,000
I'd like to meet them too.

376
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:07,200
Don't meddle in this.

377
00:28:09,440 --> 00:28:12,959
Actually, it's Lu Liuliu.

378
00:28:12,959 --> 00:28:16,140
She's pregnant. But she doesn't want me to tell others.

379
00:28:16,140 --> 00:28:19,559
Nor does she know what to do. So I bought her these books.

380
00:28:20,580 --> 00:28:22,740
- Lu Liuliu is pregnant?
- Yes.

381
00:28:22,740 --> 00:28:24,380
It's not you.

382
00:28:24,380 --> 00:28:26,540
How could it be me?

383
00:28:26,540 --> 00:28:31,800
Right. Liuliu has been popular with boys since she was young.

384
00:28:31,800 --> 00:28:36,680
Unlike you, you were rejected when you confessed to a boy in school.

385
00:28:36,680 --> 00:28:38,819
How could it be you?

386
00:28:38,819 --> 00:28:41,660
Which brat was so blind?

387
00:28:44,700 --> 00:28:47,019
He is indeed blind.

388
00:28:48,420 --> 00:28:51,039
It's your son.

389
00:28:52,760 --> 00:28:54,460
Ding Ran.

390
00:28:55,119 --> 00:28:58,059
You're holding Xile's glass.

391
00:29:03,620 --> 00:29:09,119
Oh, my God, I never want to use this glass again.

392
00:29:09,119 --> 00:29:12,199
- What's wrong with accidentally using your glass?
- You...

393
00:29:12,199 --> 00:29:15,379
Don't you have your own glass?

394
00:29:15,379 --> 00:29:18,460
Save me, save me.

395
00:29:23,099 --> 00:29:26,999
Jiang Xile, come with me if you dare.

396
00:29:26,999 --> 00:29:31,459
Ding Ran, you drank from Xile's glass. Why are you so angry?

397
00:29:31,459 --> 00:29:35,180
Baby, it's just a glass. Don't be so petty.

398
00:29:35,180 --> 00:29:38,319
- Exactly.
- Mom, Uncle Ding, don't worry.

399
00:29:38,319 --> 00:29:40,819
I promise I won't beat him to death.

400
00:29:41,780 --> 00:29:44,600
Come on. Let's talk it out.

401
00:29:44,600 --> 00:29:46,520
Baby.

402
00:29:47,480 --> 00:29:49,240
Baby.

403
00:29:49,240 --> 00:29:50,979
Baby.

404
00:29:52,279 --> 00:29:54,440
Are you disgusted with me?

405
00:29:55,119 --> 00:29:58,440
How could it be? It's just the circumstances.

406
00:29:59,400 --> 00:30:01,400
They are outside.

407
00:30:01,400 --> 00:30:04,679
I'll get you a new glass. It's just a glass.

408
00:30:05,199 --> 00:30:07,299
Baby, you're both so grown up.

409
00:30:07,299 --> 00:30:09,560
You shouldn't fuss over such small things.

410
00:30:09,560 --> 00:30:10,920
Wait a minute, wait a minute.

411
00:30:10,920 --> 00:30:13,439
I owe you a glass, right?

412
00:30:14,680 --> 00:30:16,459
Hurry up.

413
00:30:17,839 --> 00:30:20,039
It's them, it's them.

414
00:30:20,039 --> 00:30:23,340
No need. I want to give it to you, okay?

415
00:30:24,320 --> 00:30:26,439
You really need to be kissed.

416
00:30:36,720 --> 00:30:40,240
What exactly do they have against each other?

417
00:30:40,240 --> 00:30:42,599
Maybe they just don't get along.

418
00:30:42,599 --> 00:30:44,679
A pair of little foes.

419
00:30:44,679 --> 00:30:46,919
Let's go, they'll be fine.

420
00:30:51,119 --> 00:30:54,820
- We are leaving, bye.
- Bye, take care!

421
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:24,460
Why did everyone leave?

422
00:31:24,460 --> 00:31:26,619
I asked them to leave earlier.

423
00:31:31,620 --> 00:31:33,620
What are you reading?

424
00:31:33,620 --> 00:31:35,820
Nothing.
[Newborn Baby Care]

425
00:31:41,130 --> 00:31:42,510
[Newborn Baby Care]

426
00:31:43,460 --> 00:31:45,119
Why so many baby products?

427
00:31:45,119 --> 00:31:47,079
These?

428
00:31:47,739 --> 00:31:49,659
Guess why.

429
00:31:56,480 --> 00:31:59,599
Are you and Jiang Xile expanding into the baby market?

430
00:32:01,800 --> 00:32:05,660
I'll give you another chance. Think carefully.

431
00:32:07,159 --> 00:32:09,200
Someone is pregnant.

432
00:32:11,119 --> 00:32:12,939
Almost there

433
00:32:12,939 --> 00:32:15,220
Jiang Xile's mother.

434
00:32:15,939 --> 00:32:17,460
What's wrong with your brain?

435
00:32:17,460 --> 00:32:19,760
- Why do you hit me?
- What's wrong with your brain? Is it hard to guess who's pregnant?

436
00:32:19,760 --> 00:32:22,180
Who's pregnant, how would I know?

437
00:32:22,180 --> 00:32:25,940
- Me, me, me. I'm pregnant.
- Why didn't you say it earlier? You should…

438
00:32:44,540 --> 00:32:46,380
You're pregnant.

439
00:32:50,990 --> 00:32:55,739
These are all for our child?

440
00:32:56,440 --> 00:32:58,280
What else?

441
00:33:00,776 --> 00:33:06,216
♫ Listen to the sound in your heart  ♫

442
00:33:06,216 --> 00:33:10,540
♫ It seems to have some kind of penetrating power  ♫

443
00:33:10,540 --> 00:33:12,619
Qi Fei.

444
00:33:13,300 --> 00:33:17,770
♫ I will be more determined to hold you tight ♫

445
00:33:17,770 --> 00:33:20,180
Qi Fei, what are you doing?

446
00:33:22,400 --> 00:33:24,659
Let me think.

447
00:33:25,560 --> 00:33:27,320
What are you thinking about?

448
00:33:27,320 --> 00:33:31,979
♫ It's you who came into my life ♫

449
00:33:31,979 --> 00:33:34,100
Are you regretting it?

450
00:33:34,900 --> 00:33:38,559
Should we… Should we go to buy the wedding dress first or go to buy the wedding ring first?

451
00:33:38,559 --> 00:33:42,870
Do we need to book in advance for the marriage registration?

452
00:33:42,870 --> 00:33:46,920
♫ No one can replace the dream you are in ♫

453
00:33:46,920 --> 00:33:52,340
♫ I'll see you in my dreams till I wake up ♫

454
00:33:52,340 --> 00:33:54,700
I don't want to.

455
00:33:54,700 --> 00:33:56,739
What do you want to do then?

456
00:33:56,739 --> 00:33:59,540
Send a message to your ex-boyfriend, to annoy him.

457
00:33:59,540 --> 00:34:01,500
He is nothing to me.

458
00:34:02,850 --> 00:34:04,950
♫ We won't be apart again ♫

459
00:34:04,950 --> 00:34:07,380
I want you to hug me first.

460
00:34:10,580 --> 00:34:13,330
I'm going to be a dad!

461
00:34:13,330 --> 00:34:19,450
♫ Lying in your embrace gives me all the courage ♫

462
00:34:19,450 --> 00:34:22,819
♫ Let's wait for the next shooting star to see the changing times pass through your eyes ♫

463
00:34:22,819 --> 00:34:29,493
♫ Let's wait for the next shooting star to see the changing times pass through your eyes ♫

464
00:34:29,493 --> 00:34:33,232
♫ To travel with me ♫

465
00:34:33,232 --> 00:34:39,798
♫ Don't think about those profound and difficult philosophies ♫

466
00:34:39,798 --> 00:34:47,020
♫ At this moment, only you and I exist ♫

467
00:34:55,970 --> 00:35:00,480
'Traveling the Stars' - Ye Yihang

468
00:35:00,480 --> 00:35:06,136
♫ It's you who came into my life ♫

469
00:35:06,136 --> 00:35:12,803
♫ Telling me it's easy to find happiness ♫

470
00:35:12,803 --> 00:35:20,241
♫ No one can replace the dream you are in ♫

471
00:35:20,241 --> 00:35:26,163
♫ I'll see you in my dreams till I wake up ♫

472
00:35:26,163 --> 00:35:29,423
♫ Let's wait for the next shooting star to fulfill our promise ♫

473
00:35:29,423 --> 00:35:35,450
♫ Let's wait for the next shooting star to fulfill our promise ♫
